The SureFire high-capacity magazine for 5.56x45 mm (.223 Remington) ammunition, is compatible with M4/M16/AR-15 variants and other firearms that accept standard STANAG 4179 magazines. Constructed from Mil-Spec hard-anodized aluminum, they feed smoothly and reliably due to optimal geometry, non-binding coil springs, and ingenious nesting polymer followers. The long-lasting springs are cadmium coated for low friction and excellent corrosion resistance. Magazines require no lubricants and can be easily disassembled without tools for cleaning. 

SureFire High-Capacity magazines provide distinct tactical advantages: increased initial firepower in ambush situations; fewer reloads overall, which means less downtime and target distraction in a firefight; fast and easy magazine insertion, even with a closed bolt; less bulk compared to drum mags, enabling a normal weapon grip. The 60-round magazine—slightly thinner than two 30-round magazines clipped together and about the same overall length—fits in most dual magazine pouches, eliminating special carry pouches required for drum magazines.

title: For Sale:  Beware of scammers, now more then ever!!
postcontent: I have contacted 2 scammers in the last two days on armslist. I realize they have always been there, however with the crazy prices lately it seems they have come out of the woodwork. A couple suggestions. 1. After initial contact( via armslist) if their not willing to communicate via phone ...run . A scammer won't do this for fear you will ask him a simple question he can't answer. You will always get a vibe whether the seller is in the up and up, just by hearing them talk. 2. If the response you receive after initial contact says private owner...run. This is someone trying to protect their email address ,but not from spammers. Their  trying to keep their identity hidden from prosecution after they scam you. I find that honest sellers are open to all forms of communication and questions. There are alot of great sellers on here for sure. But when 800 dollar ARs start selling for 2000+ you can bet the number of scammers more then doubles as well.  Take care and best of luck to all!

title: For Sale/Trade:  SAIGA .308 AK CONVERTED CUSTOM SEMI AUTOMATIC FOLDING RIFLE NOT AR15 AK47 2 HIGH CAPACITY MAGS
postcontent:
I am listing a converted Saiga .308 Winchester AK platform semi automatic sporting rifle. This rifle has had the trigger group and pistol grip moved forward towards the traditional AK profile. The trigger group is a Tapco G2 polished and customized by Dinzag Arms. The pistol grip is Hogue. It has a chrome lined 16" barrel. The rifle performs flawlessly with no FTE or FTFs. I am including 2 24 round polymer high capacity magazines that have worked perfectly (4 are pictured, but only two are included, I have more that can be purchased along with the rifle.) The rifle includes everything you see: aluminum (US made) fore grip (with hollow compartment), bi pod, quick detach side picatinny scope rail with 4-16X Mil Dot Illuminated scope, Folding telescoping collapsible stock.

This is not an AR-15, this is a piston driven semi automatic shooting the larger .308 Winchester cartridge. This is a big rifle that is loud and throws a 2-3 foot fireball with each shot. You will get someone's attention quickly; I have had many people approach me at the range wanting to look this rifle over. the AK piston system is famous for it's reliability and ease of use, cleaning and repair. It drives a bullet that is up to 5 times heavier than the AR-15 and has up to 1500 more foot/pounds of energy with each shot. This is a big boy rifle, but the simplicity of the AK system is great for newer semi automatic rifle owners. This is a rare rifle, especially with the conversion already completed. 

I will meet FTF with TN residents, and I can work through an FFL to ship it anywhere in the country ( except CA, IL and other cities/states/etc... with laws preventing such a rifle. Know your laws.) 

I am not desperate to sell or needing cash now, I just do not shoot this rifle often and will use the funds to upgrade a long range bolt project I am working on. I feel bad this rifle is so under used, they are made to shoot. Please email me with any questions or offers.

title: For Sale:  YHM AR15 M4 With Magazines and Trijicon Acog With Docter Red Dot
postcontent:
Up for sale is my personal Yankee Hill Machine AR15. It is their Smooth Carbine model 8200. This is a complete high end factory rifle, not something put together in a basement. If you are looking for a top of the line rifle, this is it. One thing I love about this rifle is how comfortable it is in the hand, a lot of that is due to the handguard which allows you to have rails where you need them and no in places that interfere with your hand or rest. The 8200 also features their Black Diamond fluting which reduces weight, increases heat dissipation and looks awesome. It has an excellent trigger and is very accurate. I am able to consistently ring steel at 500+ yards with this rig. It only has 330 rounds of factory ammo fired, and was always properly cleaned and maintained. It is as close to new as you will find a rifle that has been shot.

I have added a few upgrades to make the rifle even better. I installed a Troy Battle Ax stock which gives a great cheek weld and also makes it more effective as a CQB rifle. I added a Ergo Grip which is a big comfort increase over the stock grip. The factory stock, grip and hardshell case are included as well. I am also including a windowed PMAG, along with 2 Colt magazines, one Bushmaster and one NHMTG

The optic is a Trijicon TA01NSN-DOC. It has been upgraded with a GG&G Accucam Mount with integral lense covers. The optic has an MSRP of $1,800, and the mount sells for $192. It comes complete with its Pelican case, all paperwork including decals, tools and Docter information. This is the best optic I have ever used on an AR and it is zeroed and ready to go. It allows you to make quick shots at 600 yards plus, and then use the Docter for close engagements. Another benefit of the YHM 8200 is the built in front and rear back up iron sights, so you will have three sighting options on this rifle

Please keep in mind this setup retailed for over $3,500 BEFORE the proposed ban. Don't waste your money on a Frankenstein build that you can't trust the quality of, with garbage Chinese optics and an unknown builder. Invest in a rifle that will only continue to go up in value and will give you years of trouble free shooting.
